The paper focuses on cybersecurity education and accreditation, which is most closely related to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. However, it also discusses the teaching of cybersecurity within general computer science, which could fall under cs.ED (Education), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also touches on policy and politics related to cybersecurity education, which could be relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
